== Intent ==

illustrate building a web applications with Seam


== Languages ==

* [[Language:Java]]
* [[Language:HQL]]
* [[Language:XHTML]]

== Features ==

* [[101feature:Company]]
* [[101feature:Total]]
* [[101feature:Cut]]
* [[101feature:Database]]
* [[101feature:Authentication]]


== Motivation == 

This is a simple web implementation of the basic 101companies-features, plus 
database persistence and authentication/authorization feaures, using  
the SEAM framework.

== Usage ==

=== Requirements ===

	JBOSS-4.2.x (http://sourceforge.net/projects/jboss/files/JBoss/JBoss-4.2.3.GA)

=== Build === 

	(a) change the build.properties file, reviewing the jboss.home property that must refer 
	to the place where you have installed the jboss distribution. 
	
	(b) run "ant deploy" in the root directory of the SEAM implementation of 101companies
	
=== Acessing the system ===

 	(a) start a web-browser
 	
 	(b) inform the URL http://localhost:8080/seam  
 	
 	(c) you should able to access the system using either the "admin" or "user" account. If you 
 	try to cut salaries when logged in as a "user", an exception should be thrown. 
 	
=== Notes ===

	(a) Whenever the application is deployed, the script import-dev.sql loads the test data.  
 	
 	
